org.latency4j

Class LatencyRequirement

  • java.lang.Object
    • org.latency4j.LatencyRequirement
  • Direct Known Subclasses:
    CappedLatencyRequirement, StatisticalLatencyRequirement

    public abstract class LatencyRequirement
extends java.lang.Object

    Abstract representation of a latency requirement. Please note that instances of this class must be initialised before use.

    • Method Detail

      • init

        public void init()

        Initialises the instance. This involves performing the following actions:

        • Verify that all fields have been assigned valid values.
        • Test for an override of the persistence manager. If none is provided, the default persistence manager is used. This, by default, writes and reads durations from the system's temporary folder as identified by the java property Latency4JConstants.JAVA_TMP_FILE_FOLDER.

      • setIgnoreErrors

        public void setIgnoreErrors(boolean ignoreErrors)

        Specifies if monitors of this requirement should report abnormal task terminations brought about by exceptions and errors.

        Parameters:
        ignoreErrors - True if monitors of this requirement should ignore errors, and False otherwise.
        See Also:
        isIgnoreErrors()

      • isIgnoreErrors

        public boolean isIgnoreErrors()

        Indicates if monitors of this requirement should report abnormal task terminations due to exceptions and errors. Except explicitly enabled, this method will return True. This is to ensure that error reporting only occurs if requested explicitly.

        Returns:
        True if monitors of this requirement should ignore errors, and False otherwise.
        See Also:
        setIgnoreErrors(boolean)

      • getAlertHandlers

        public java.util.List<AlertHandler> getAlertHandlers()

        Provides access to the list of alert handlers associated to the instance. These are the handlers which have been designated to receive notifications related to this requirement.

        Returns:
        The collection of alert handlers responsible for processing alerts related to this requirement.

      • setAlertHandlers

        public void setAlertHandlers(java.util.List<AlertHandler> missedTargetHandlers)

        Associates a list of alert handlers to this instance. These are the handlers which will process notifications related to this requirement.

        Parameters:
        missedTargetHandlers - The alert handlers to be associated to this requirement.

      • setPersistenceManager

        public void setPersistenceManager(WorkDurationPersistenceManager persistenceManager)

        Specifies a persistence manager for persisting and reading durations of tasks falling under the remit of this requirement. This method can be used to override the use of the default (file-based) persistence manager.

        Parameters:
        persistenceManager - The persistence manager that is to be used to store and read durations of tasks falling under the remit of this requirement.
        See Also:
        getPersistenceManager()
